In[]:
import osmnx as ox
import networkx as nx

# Obtain the graph
G = ox.graph_from_place('Amsterdam', retain_all= False, truncate_by_edge=False,

                        simplify=True, custom_filter='["waterway"~"canal"]')

origin_point = (52.362935, 4.884141)  
destination_point = (52.373278, 4.900836)  

orig = ox.distance.nearest_nodes(G, origin_point[1], origin_point[0])
dest = ox.distance.nearest_nodes(G, destination_point[1], destination_point[0])

route = nx.shortest_path(G, orig, dest)

fig, ax = ox.plot_graph_route(G, route, route_linewidth=6, node_size=3, bgcolor='k')

nodes_coordinates = [G.nodes[node] for node in route]

avg_latitude = sum(node['y'] for node in nodes_coordinates) / len(nodes_coordinates)

avg_longitude = sum(node['x'] for node in nodes_coordinates) / len(nodes_coordinates)

 

print(f"Center latitude: {avg_latitude}, Center longitude: {avg_longitude}")

# The tramsstops and busstops in the the distance of 1000m from the startpoint

ox.config(use_cache=True, log_console=True)
startpoint= (52.362942, 4.884304)
distance = 1000 
tags = {'highway' : 'bus_stop',
        'railway': 'tram_stop'}

all_pois = ox.features_from_point(center_point=startpoint, tags=tags, dist=distance)
all_pois.loc[(all_pois['highway'] == 'bus_stop')]
all_pois.loc[(all_pois['railway'] == 'tram_stop')]

bus_stops = all_pois.loc[all_pois['highway'] == 'bus_stop']
tram_stops = all_pois.loc[all_pois['railway'] == 'tram_stop']

csv_file_path = 'bus_stops.csv'
csv_file_path = 'Trams_stops.csv'

bus_stops.to_csv(csv_file_path, index=False)
tram_stops.to_csv(csv_file_path, index=False)

print(f"Data has been exported to {csv_file_path}")

# The closest Tramstop tot the startpoint
import pandas as pd
import geopy.distance

# Read CSV data into a DataFrame
df = pd.read_csv("/Users/fatimazohra/Desktop/Trams_stops_startpoint.csv")

# Define the startpoint (latitude and longitude)
startpoint = (52.362942, 4.884304)

 #Verwijder eventuele voorloopspaties in de kolomnamen
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()

# Definieer het startpunt (latitude en longitude)
startpoint = (52.362942, 4.884304)

# Functie om de haversine-afstand tussen twee punten te berekenen
def haversine_distance(point1, point2):
    return geopy.distance.geodesic(point1, point2).m

# Functie om de punten in de kolom 'geometry' te splitsen en de afstand te berekenen
def calculate_distance(geometry):
    lat_lon_str = geometry.split("(")[1].split(")")[0]
    lat, lon = map(float, lat_lon_str.split())
    point = (lat, lon)
    return haversine_distance(startpoint, point)

#How many people transported per hour assuming they go from the startpoint bus/tramstop to the endpoint bus/tramstop 

average_passenger_capacity_tram = 50  #(source:https://over.gvb.nl/content/uploads/2018/08)
frequency = 9  #(source:https://9292.nl/reisadvies) #we see only tram 2 go directly to there
passenger_demand = 0.8  

people_per_tram = average_passenger_capacity_tram * passenger_demand
people_per_hour = people_per_tram * frequency

print(f"Estimated number of people transported in one hour: {people_per_hour}")

Estimated number of people transported in one hour: 360.0

G = ox.graph_from_address('Kattenburgerplein, Amsterdam', network_type='drive')
ox.plot_graph(G)

origin_node = ox.distance.nearest_nodes(G, 4.892411, 52.369797)
destination_node = ox.distance.nearest_nodes(G, 4.895702, 52.373828)
centre_output = ox.distance.nearest_nodes(G, 4.892411, 52.369797)

start_centrality = nx.closeness_centrality(G, u=origin_node)
end_centrality = nx.closeness_centrality(G, u=destination_node)
centre_centrality = nx.closeness_centrality(G, u=centre_output)

print(start_centrality)
print(end_centrality)
print(centre_centrality)

  1. Find all cafes, restaurants near the finish line. Walking time smaller than 10 minutes
In[]:
ox.config(use_cache=True, log_console=True)
startpoint= (52.362942, 4.884304)
distance = 1000 
tags = {'amenity' : 'cafe',
        'amenity' : 'restaurant'}

all_pois = ox.features_from_point(center_point=startpoint, tags=tags, dist=distance)
import geopy
# Create a function to calculate walking time in seconds
def calculate_walking_time(point1, point2, walking_speed=1.4):
    # Calculate the great-circle distance between two points in meters
    geodist = geopy.distance.geodesic(point1, point2).meters
    # Calculate walking time in seconds
    walking_time = geodist / walking_speed
    return walking_time

# Calculate the walking time to each POI and add it to the DataFrame
walking_speed = 1.4  # Estimated walking speed in meters per second
all_pois['walking_time'] = all_pois['geometry'].centroid.apply(
    lambda geom: calculate_walking_time(startpoint, (geom.y, geom.x), walking_speed)
)

# Filter the POIs based on walking time (10 minutes or less)
nearby_pois = all_pois[all_pois['walking_time'] <= 600]

# Separate the POIs into cafes and restaurants
cafes = nearby_pois[nearby_pois['amenity'] == 'cafe']
restaurants = nearby_pois[nearby_pois['amenity'] == 'restaurant']


csv_file_path = 'cafes.csv'
csv_file_path = 'restaurants.csv'

cafes.to_csv(csv_file_path, index=False)
print(f"Data has been exported to {csv_file_path}")

restaurants.to_csv(csv_file_path, index=False)
print(f"Data has been exported to {csv_file_path}")

Data has been exported to restaurants.csv
Data has been exported to restaurants.csv
